    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Bergeranthus rehneltianus are wounds, including cuts and lacerations. Bergeranthus rehneltianus is also effective in treating burns, particularly second-degree burns, reducing the risk of infection and promoting faster healing. It has been used to treat skin irritations, such as eczema and dermatitis, by reducing inflammation and promoting the regeneration of skin cells. Additionally, Bergeranthus rehneltianus has been used to treat digestive issues, including diarrhea and irritable bowel syndrome, by reducing inflammation and promoting the growth of beneficial gut bacteria. Warts and fungal infections, including athlete's foot, have also been successfully treated with Bergeranthus rehneltianus.",
