    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Bergeranthus rehneltianus are anti-inflammatory effects, which suggest its potential in treating conditions such as arthritis, and antioxidant properties, indicating its ability to protect against oxidative stress and cell damage. This is largely attributed to the presence of flavonoids, such as kaempferol and quercetin, and saponins, like 3-O-acetyl-6\u03b1-hydroxy-\u03b2-sitosterol. Antimicrobial properties, including antibacterial and antifungal activities, allow the plant to combat infections and promote wound healing. The anti-proliferative effects of Bergeranthus rehneltianus may also contribute to its potential in cancer prevention and treatment. Additionally, the plant's ability to modulate the immune system, with immunomodulatory properties, makes it a promising candidate for the development of new immunotherapies.",
