    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Bergeranthus rehneltianus are flavonoids, phenolic acids, and triterpenoids. These compounds exhibit potent antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties, making them valuable for wound healing, antimicrobial resistance, and reducing oxidative stress. Flavonoids, specifically kaempferol and quercetin, have been shown to inhibit the growth of certain bacteria and fungi, while phenolic acids, such as ferulic acid, have been found to possess strong antioxidant activity. Triterpenoids, including ursolic acid, have been demonstrated to have anti-inflammatory effects by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. These bioactive compounds contribute to the plant's traditional use in treating various ailments, including skin conditions and infections.",
