    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Bergeranthus rehneltianus are infusion and decoction made by steeping the leaves in hot water to extract its bioactive compounds, such as flavonoids and phenolic acids, which are valued for their antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. A tea is also prepared by infusing the leaves in hot water to make a medicinal drink that is used to treat various health issues. Tincture is another preparation made by extracting the active compounds from the leaves using solvents like ethanol or glycerin, which is used to create a concentrated liquid extract for medicinal purposes. Salve is prepared by infusing the leaves in oil to create a topical cream or ointment that is used to treat skin conditions and wounds. These preparations are valued for their potential health benefits and are used in traditional medicine to treat various health conditions.",
